# Git Assignment - <Your GitHub Username>

### a. What is an issue?
An issue is a way to track tasks, enhancements, bugs, or any other to-do items within a repository. It allows project members to discuss and collaborate on these topics.

### c. Describe the steps to open a pull request.
1. Push your changes to a branch in your repository.
2. Navigate to the repository on GitHub.
3. Click on the "Pull requests" tab.
4. Click "New pull request."
5. Select the branch you want to merge into the main branch.
6. Review the changes and add a descriptive title and comment.
7. Click "Create pull request."